{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"15de3f7e-0ab1-447c-a1fc-4f02675d5074","content":"In your `App.xaml.cs`, override `CreateWindow` and subscribe to the lifecycle events on the returned `Window`:\n\n```csharp\nprotected override Window CreateWindow(IActivationState? activationState)\n{\n    var window = base.CreateWindow(activationState);\n\n    window.Created      += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Created\");\n    window.Activated    += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Activated\");\n    window.Deactivated  += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Deactivated\");\n    window.Stopped      += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Stopped\");\n    window.Resumed      += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Resumed\");\n    window.Destroying   += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Destroying\");\n    window.Backgrounding += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Backgrounding\");\n\n    return window;\n}\n```\n\n**Typical transition order:**\n\n| Action | Events fired |\n|---|---|\n| App launch | `Created` → `Activated` |\n| User switches away | `Deactivated` → `Stopped` |\n| User returns | `Resumed` → `Activated` |\n| App closed | `Deactivated` → `Stopped` → `Destroying` |\n\n> **Note:** `Backgrounding` is iOS/Mac Catalyst only — use it to save state before the OS may terminate your app.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"cd97fd8d-f469-4e95-82b6-037e02e6bdd9","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about .NET MAUI Window lifecycle events and how to subscribe to them for logging/debugging. This is a general knowledge question - I can answer it directly without needing to search the codebase.","outputTokens":413,"requestId":"1032:22188A:149CF0E:1736E90:69FD343E"},"id":"e7150a2c-fc05-43a1-b79a-1bda6667566b","timestamp":"2026-05-08T00:54:31.325Z","parentId":"3cefe937-7b5f-4062-b2e7-949ad8af1b68"}
